					</div>

					<div class="comment-text">
						<p>I&#8217;m not Michael, but I bought a Vita-Mix 5200 a few years ago and absolutely love it. Is it over the top for a home cook? Not any more than any other tool. If you can afford it, go for it.</p>
<p>I love it for making blended soups, and it&#8217;s unsurpassed for anything that involves reconstituted dried chiles (no bits of skin left un-ground, I&#8217;ve never seen another blender do that.) Great for any sort of blended sauces, grinding nuts, and making smoothies (no frozen chunks of fruit floating around.)</p>
					</div>

										<div class="comment-buttons">							<a class="comment-button comment-link" href="http://ruhlman.com/2010/04/my-essential-kitchen-tools.html/comment-page-1#comment-57478">Link</a>					</div>
