						<span class="date">April 12, 2010 at 12:19 pm</span>
					</div>

					<div class="comment-text">
						<p>+1 for a good blender.  I&#8217;ve owned a lot of cheap blenders over the years, but being such, the ones I didn&#8217;t burn up I didn&#8217;t bother to use because I was expecting them croak, blend badly, and be a pain to clean.</p>
<p>I finally begrudgingly spent the money and bought a VM5200 a few months ago, and I love it and use it a couple of times a day.  This thing would blend rocks if I asked it to, and cleanup is dead simple (bit of water, drop of soap, crank on full, rinse).  </p>
<p>I wish I&#8217;d have bought one years ago.</p>
