						<cite class="fn">Jose Canseco</cite>
						<span class="date">April 12, 2010 at 1:34 pm</span>
					</div>

					<div class="comment-text">
						<p>All-Clad manufactures great cookware (much of it in the USA), my favorites are my 3 qt saucier and saute pan.  </p>
<p>Recently I&#8217;ve started collecting Falk Culinair copper cookware, which is equally if not more expensive than All-Clad.  That&#8217;s just a personal preference though, since I like the temperature response, feel, and looks of heavy copper.</p>
<p>Lifetime warranty for high quality cookware is a given &#8211; don&#8217;t consider brands that don&#8217;t offer it.  Well made pots and pan SHOULDN&#8217;T ever need replacing in your lifetime&#8230;unless they&#8217;re abused.</p>
					</div>

