						<p>My single favorite items are the most basic.  </p>
<p>My knives of course are #1.  I don&#8217;t own a food processor, so use them for everything.  I have only 4 &#8211; chef&#8217;s knife, paring knife, bread knife, and large chinese cleaver.</p>
<p>#2 are my mortar &amp; pestles &#8211; my big granite mortar &amp; pestle, which I use for making Thai curries and pesto, and my small mortar &amp; pestle, which I use for grinding pepper, mashing garlic and ginger, etc.  Love the control these give me.  And my little used, but lovely clay mortar &amp; wood pestle, which I use only for making green papaya salad.</p>
<p>There are many other things I love, including the workhorse cast iron skillet I bought at a garage sale for $5, my kitchenaid mixer, etc &#8211; but the knives and the M&amp;P are my must-have, top 2, never-gonna-give-them-up implements.</p>
